text.tspan: Vaccination coverage (DPT) vs. share of the population living in extreme
DPT vaccination coverage is the share of children between 12 and 23 months who received vaccinations against diphteria,
pertussis, and tetanus. Extreme poverty is defined as living on less than 1.90 international-$ per day.
